  {
    "index": 3,
    "hash": "M20rzkAvV2IjJlnGXIGVL/ZsE3M=",
    "timestampUtcMs": "2026-05-13T13:00:35.000Z",
    "action": {
      "type": "SET_CONTENT",
      "input": {
        "content": "# facet model provides configurable classification dimensions\n\n`powerhouse/facet` is the simplest model \u2014 it defines classification dimensions (like \"Region\", \"Industry\", \"Size\") with selectable options. Other models reference facets for targeting and configuration.\n\n## State Shape\n\n```graphql\ntype FacetState {\n    id: PHID!\n    name: String!\n    description: String\n    lastModified: DateTime!\n    options: [FacetOption!]!\n}\n\ntype FacetOption {\n    id: OID!\n    label: String!\n    description: String\n    displayOrder: Int\n    isDefault: Boolean!\n}\n```\n\n## Modules (2)\n\n| Module | Operations | Purpose |\n|--------|-----------|---------|\n| facet-management | 2 | Set facet name, description |\n| option-management | 4 | Add/update/remove/reorder options |\n\n## Referenced By\n\n- ResourceTemplate.`facetBindings.facetType: PHID` \u2192 this model\n- ServiceOffering.`facetBindings.facetType: PHID` \u2192 this model\n- ResourceInstance.`configuration` uses facet categories\n- SubscriptionInstance services have `facetSelections`\n\n---\n\nTopics:\n- [[schema design]]\n- [[object relations]]",
        "updatedAt": "2026-05-13T13:00:35.000Z"
      },
      "timestampUtcMs": "2026-05-13T13:00:35.000Z"
    }
  },
